        "id": 7771,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2004-11-29T21:58:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes, folks, now you can play it. I made the grid for them using Zinks LBArchitect, and the scene with the moved trunks with my LBA Scene Manager. The .ZIP file, with the appropriate .LUN (scene), and .GR2 (grid) files is attached in this post.<br>\nAlso, for best effect (to remove the S symbol on the top, as it wasnt present in that version, at least, before you open the door), replace the entries 191-194 in the LBA 2 SPRITES.HQR file with 4 1x1 sprites.<br>\nSo, I think a dream has come true tonight.</p>\n<p>Im looking forward to hearing from you all.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,<br>\nJoo de Cames (OBrasilo).</p>\n<p><a class=\"attachment\" href=\"/uploads/short-url/7kZtw7wYrItqehDykodXCCYfmnn.zip\">sewers_prev.zip</a> (7.85 KB)</p>",
